word_mean_info__list.difference: 着重自愿、令人愉快或急切地去行动。
使用广泛，侧重不受约束，行动不为其他影响所左右。

bilingual.source: She made a voluntary donation to the charity.
bilingual.target: 她向慈善机构进行了自愿的捐赠。

bilingual.source: Participation in the event is completely voluntary.
bilingual.target: 参加这个活动是完全自愿的。

bilingual.source: It was organized on a voluntary basis.
bilingual.target: 它是在自愿的基础上组织起来的。

bilingual.source: Is this a mandatory or voluntary pay cut?
bilingual.target: 这次减薪是强制的还是自愿的? ?。

bilingual.source: Your participation in this study is voluntary.
bilingual.target: 你们的参与是完全自愿的。

bilingual.source: Our approach is educational and wholly voluntary.
bilingual.target: 我们的方法是说教式的完全自愿的。

bilingual.source: Even our full-time staff work on a voluntary basis.
bilingual.target: 即使我们的专职工作人员在自愿的基础上。

bilingual.source: The only question they are asked is, “Is it voluntary?
bilingual.target: 唯一一个他们会问的问题就是：“离婚是自愿的吗？”

yingyinNormal.zh: 是自愿取证。对，自愿取证。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay. Did you discuss your voluntary deposition with anyone before today?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好，在今天之前，你跟任何人讨论过今天的自愿取证会吗？

yingyinNormal.en: And now you have a new job? Unfortunately, it was a paralegal job. Voluntary.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你现在找到新工作了是吗？很不幸，那是份律师助理的工作，是志愿工作的。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
